# Pin the tools/list snapshot gate to LF. registry-snapshot-test.mjs emits the
# canonical form with `\n` (JSON.stringify), so the committed fixture and the
# harness must materialize as LF on every OS — otherwise core.autocrlf on the
# windows-latest `gate` leg checks the fixture out as CRLF and the byte-identical
# comparison fails on `\r` alone (content is identical). The git blobs are already
# LF; this only normalizes the working-tree copy so the blocking gate is
# deterministic cross-OS.
tools-list-snapshot.json text eol=lf
registry-snapshot-test.mjs text eol=lf
